
MAX889 Charge pump IC

We have MAX889S variant.

PART    FREQUENCY C FLY C OUT C IN REGULATED C IN FREE-RUN
MAX889S 1MHz      2.2μF 10μF  10μF           2.2μF


Output Ripple mV  vs Load Current substituting  C OUT and a load I=50-100mA , ripple ought to be 5-8mV.  Is this OK?

We don't know because we don't know exactly what's inside and there is no indication on the encoder's datasheet.  Ripple should be fundamentally located @fOSC which is 1MHz, so filtering should be straightforward given our estimate for encoder signals of ~   DO SUMS

From the datasheet,

\begin{equation*}
R_1 \le \frac{V_{ref}}{30\m uA}
\end{equation*}

\begin{equation*}
R_2 \lt \frac{-V_{out}}{30\mu A}
\end{equation*}

Calculate for 12V input and reference at 5V.

\begin{equation*}
R_1 \le \frac{5}{30\m uA} \eq 167kR
\end{equation*}

\begin{equation*}
R_2 \lt \frac{5}{30\mu A} \eq 167kR
\end{equation*}

Choose R1 to be less than or equal 100kR.

\begin{equation*}
R_1 \eq 100kR
\end{equation*}

\begin{equation*}
R_2 \eq R_1 \left ( \frac{V_{out}}{- V_{ref}} \right ) = \frac{100e3 -5 }{ -5} = 100kR
\end{equation*}


Calculate for 12V input and reference at 12V.

\begin{equation*}
R_1 \le \frac{12}{30\m uA} \eq 400kR
\end{equation*}

\begin{equation*}
R_2 \lt \frac{5}{30\mu A} \eq 167kR
\end{equation*}


Design input filter using spice.

